@startuml DFD_Level2_Authentication_Process
!define RECTANGLE class

skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

' External Entity
actor "Pet Owner" as Owner <<External Entity>>

' Level 2 Processes for Authentication (1.0)
rectangle "1.1\nValidate\nInput Data" as Validate <<Process>>
rectangle "1.2\nHash Password\n(Bcrypt)" as Hash <<Process>>
rectangle "1.3\nCheck User\nExistence" as CheckUser <<Process>>
rectangle "1.4\nCreate User\nRecord" as CreateUser <<Process>>
rectangle "1.5\nGenerate JWT\nToken" as GenJWT <<Process>>
rectangle "1.6\nVerify Password" as VerifyPass <<Process>>
rectangle "1.7\nValidate Token\n& Session" as ValidateToken <<Process>>

' Data Stores
database "D1: Users" as D1 <<Data Store>>
database "D8: Sessions/Cache\n(Redis)" as D8 <<Data Store>>

' Registration Flow
Owner --> Validate : Email, Password\nName, Phone
Validate --> Hash : Validated Data
Hash --> CheckUser : Email + Hashed Password
CheckUser --> D1 : Check Email
D1 --> CheckUser : User Exists?
CheckUser --> CreateUser : New User Data\n(if not exists)
CreateUser --> D1 : Store User Record
CreateUser --> GenJWT : User ID
GenJWT --> D8 : Store Session\n(7-day expiry)
GenJWT --> Owner : JWT Token

' Login Flow
Owner --> Validate : Email, Password\n(Login)
Validate --> CheckUser : Validated Credentials
CheckUser --> D1 : Query User
D1 --> CheckUser : User Record
CheckUser --> VerifyPass : User Hash + Input Password
VerifyPass --> GenJWT : User ID\n(if valid)
GenJWT --> Owner : JWT Token\n(if authenticated)
VerifyPass --> Owner : Error: Invalid Credentials\n(if failed)

' Token Validation Flow
Owner --> ValidateToken : JWT Token\n(API Request)
ValidateToken --> D8 : Check Session
D8 --> ValidateToken : Session Data
ValidateToken --> Owner : Authorized\n(User ID extracted)
ValidateToken --> Owner : Error: Token Expired/Invalid

note right of Validate
  Level 2 DFD: Authentication (1.0)
  
  Sub-processes:
  1.1 - Input validation (email format, password strength)
  1.2 - Password hashing (bcrypt cost=12)
  1.3 - User existence check
  1.4 - User creation
  1.5 - JWT generation (7-day expiry)
  1.6 - Password verification
  1.7 - Token validation
end note

note bottom of D1
  Stores: user_id, email, password_hash,
  name, phone, role, created_at
end note

note bottom of D8
  Redis cache stores JWT sessions
  with 7-day TTL for quick validation
end note

@enduml
